diff:1666549379:1666549379:=1,86d0%0a%3c (:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0a%3c Status: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!{$:Category}]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Open or Close the Lights%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: rubyd%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c A summary of substitution of "turn on/off" with "close/open" in mixed English dialects. %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Usage of the phrase "open the light" and "close the light" rather than the standard English phrase "turn off/turn on the light" is present in a variety of English dialects, including but not limited to pidgin-Hawaiian, Quebecois English, and Filipino English (1). There is no singular origin point for the phrase, and its region of usage is debated, though there are multiple accounts of it being common in New Jersey, USA. The most common hypothesis that ties the varied environments of the construct together is the theory that "open/close the light" is a metaphrase (a direct translation from another language) (2). This is seemingly supported by case studies of some particular dialects, notably Quebecois, in which the English "open the light" phrase can be directly traced from French's literal "ouvre la lumiere" (3). However, there are some dialects for which this theory is opposed, such as in Russian, wherein direct translation for the Russian phrase of the same meaning has more similarities with "turn on/off" than with "open/close"(1).%0a%3c %0a%3c 1. https://english.stackexchange.com/questions/21318/close-the-light-regionalism-or-mere-oddity#comment178624_21318%0a%3c 2. https://usingaborrowedlanguage.wordpress.com/2013/07/20/open-the-light/%0a%3c 3. https://ask.metafilter.com/9204/Regional-Linguistics%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: A:)%0a%3c (:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversityOfEnglish:)%0a%3c (:Title: Open or Close the Lights:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
